TSHAKHUMA Tsha Madzivhandila have fired coach Moma Medic. On Tursday the club announced that they have suspended the coach with immediate effect due to the conflicts within the team. The former Orlando Pirates coach on Friday appeared infront of the club DC and was found guilty. According to a statement issued by the club on their social media account, the coach was found guilty of misconduct and his contract was terminated. “The Coach, Mr Moma Medic, has been found guilty of gross misconduct and, as a result, his contract has been terminated with immediate effect. "Phuti Mohafe will take over as a caretaker coach. We wish the coach the best in his future endeavours,” read the club statement.